	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr. before 100. His title is given as in SIG(3) 715 from Rhegium, which Dittenberger dates before 100 from the lettering. Perhaps identifiable with the Cn. Auf[idius . . . ] named in the SC de agro Pergameno in 129. See Sherk, RDGE no. 12, pp. 63-73. (RS, MS-RP 1.275; LRT) On the date, see M'. Aquillius (10) above.\n" .
